reviews.review_text:
Amazing recording of a great show. I love how audible Bob's guitar is in many 1972 shows: just listen to his work in Bertha, Don't Ease Me In, it's more lead fills than rhythm. Even when he plays more traditional rhythm guitar, like Brown Eyed, it's still a lot more interesting that most rhythm guitar.
Charle Miller and SIRMick = awesome.
